1️) QR screenshot / photo reuse (MOST COMMON)

Attack
	Someone takes a photo of the QR
	Tries to scan it later or on another device

Mitigation (mandatory)
	Short TTL (≤ 5 min)
	One-time SID

Status transition (ACTIVE → USED)

2) Man-in-the-middle (MITM)

Attack
	Attacker intercepts traffic
	Modifies redirect

Reality
	HTTPS + TLS 1.2+ prevents this
	HSTS blocks downgrade

Mitigation
	Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000
	
3) Replay from another device

Attack
	Attacker scans QR
	Victim scans same QR later

Mitigation
	Mark SID as USED on first success
	Bind SID to device (soft → hard)	

Reject The Request from API

4) Fake browser / script call

Attack
	Curl / Postman calls /start?sid=...
Mitigation
	User-Agent validation
	TLS fingerprint
	Rate limiting

Challenge escalation if suspicious

📌 Even if this succeeds: They still cannot complete KYC.  e-NINSHO app won’t authenticate them

5) Redirect manipulation

Attack
	Open valid SID but redirect to attacker app

Mitigation
	Redirect URL is hardcoded server-side
	Never derived from request

